1
00:00:02,040 --> 00:00:03,040
Welcome...

2
00:00:04,010 --> 00:00:05,010
What?

3
00:00:05,680 --> 00:00:08,310
San Wol, you don't look so good.

4
00:00:08,610 --> 00:00:09,780
Is something wrong?

5
00:00:09,780 --> 00:00:12,320
Tae Pyung, did you know about it too?

6
00:00:12,480 --> 00:00:13,620
About what?

7
00:00:13,950 --> 00:00:16,820
That "Robot Coin" or whatever it's called.

8
00:00:17,160 --> 00:00:18,620
It was a complete scam.

9
00:00:18,820 --> 00:00:20,560
What? That was a scam?

10
00:00:21,160 --> 00:00:22,730
What are you talking about?

11
00:00:24,930 --> 00:00:27,130
I'm so furious. Goodness.

12
00:00:28,000 --> 00:00:30,440
I lost all my money.

13
00:00:30,700 --> 00:00:32,840
Tae Pyung, are you telling me
you really didn't know?

14
00:00:33,070 --> 00:00:36,140
There's no way I would've told you
if I knew it was a scam.

15
00:00:37,140 --> 00:00:40,010
See? This is why I told you
not to do it in the first place.

16
00:00:40,410 --> 00:00:41,610
No, it's not that.

17
00:00:41,680 --> 00:00:44,580
I'm asking if James,
the guy you introduced me to,

18
00:00:44,580 --> 00:00:46,080
is a scammer.

19
00:00:46,150 --> 00:00:48,350
Him? That's ridiculous.

20
00:00:49,020 --> 00:00:50,720
You must be mistaken.

21
00:00:51,060 --> 00:00:53,990
Besides, he even deposited
all that money for you.

22
00:00:54,760 --> 00:00:57,800
Well, I guess that's true, but...

23
00:00:57,860 --> 00:01:00,330
And the decision to invest
was entirely yours.

24
00:01:01,200 --> 00:01:04,640
Besides, James is loaded.
Why would he need to scam anyone?

25
00:01:04,770 --> 00:01:07,010
Look, I don't care about all that.

26
00:01:07,070 --> 00:01:10,480
Just get my money back.
My hard-earned money.

27
00:01:10,710 --> 00:01:11,910
Give me a little time.

28
00:01:12,810 --> 00:01:15,450
I'll call James and see what's going on.

29
00:01:17,980 --> 00:01:21,590
But it's not like he created the crypto,

30
00:01:21,820 --> 00:01:23,520
so we can't really hold him responsible.

31
00:01:24,520 --> 00:01:28,960
Yes, I guess you have a point, but...

32
00:01:30,460 --> 00:01:34,500
Just call him already.
I don't even have his number.

33
00:01:34,900 --> 00:01:37,940
Wait, I think he gave me a business card,

34
00:01:38,300 --> 00:01:40,740
but I can't find it anywhere now.

35
00:01:46,480 --> 00:01:48,310
Hello?

36
00:01:49,710 --> 00:01:50,720
Oh, hey...

37
00:01:51,620 --> 00:01:53,520
Okay.

38
00:01:56,550 --> 00:01:58,760
- He's Korean-American, you know.
- Right.

39
00:01:58,790 --> 00:02:01,430
He's heading to America now,
so I think he's on a plane.

40
00:02:01,490 --> 00:02:02,690
The connection is poor.

41
00:02:03,430 --> 00:02:04,900
Then what was that "okay" about?

42
00:02:06,730 --> 00:02:09,300
That was the in-flight announcement.
You know, the announcement.

43
00:02:10,070 --> 00:02:13,240
Or was it?
Oh, it's exhausting trying to fool her.

44
00:02:14,410 --> 00:02:16,940
Anyway, once you get in touch with James,

45
00:02:17,280 --> 00:02:20,080
please make sure you get
my money back, Tae Pyung.

46
00:02:20,250 --> 00:02:21,810
Of course I will.

47
00:02:23,010 --> 00:02:24,850
Gosh, San Wol.

48
00:02:25,380 --> 00:02:27,990
You look so worn out already.

49
00:02:28,920 --> 00:02:30,620
You know what?

50
00:02:30,620 --> 00:02:33,060
When you've lost your appetite,
this here...

51
00:02:33,160 --> 00:02:36,160
You just put this rolled omelet
over some rice,

52
00:02:36,160 --> 00:02:37,600
and that'll bring your appetite
right back.

53
00:02:40,130 --> 00:02:41,470
Tae Pyung.

54
00:02:42,730 --> 00:02:46,440
You're the only one who really gets me.

55
00:02:47,310 --> 00:02:49,370
I was so embarrassed
about losing all the money...

56
00:02:49,670 --> 00:02:51,280
that I couldn't tell anyone.

57
00:02:51,640 --> 00:02:53,010
I've been so stressed.

58
00:02:53,210 --> 00:02:56,250
You poor thing.
You must've been so stressed.

59
00:02:57,050 --> 00:02:59,780
Even my own daughter gives me
such a hard time about it.

60
00:03:00,020 --> 00:03:03,690
It's my money to lose,
so why is she freaking out?

61
00:03:04,160 --> 00:03:07,160
She isn't threatening to go to the police,
is she?

62
00:03:07,490 --> 00:03:11,460
No, because then
the Chairman would find out,

63
00:03:12,100 --> 00:03:14,300
and I could get kicked out of the house.

64
00:03:16,000 --> 00:03:17,600
I'm upset,

65
00:03:17,800 --> 00:03:20,640
but I must keep it to myself.
What else can I do?

66
00:03:22,640 --> 00:03:24,210
You must have been so upset.

67
00:03:24,910 --> 00:03:27,910
That's what she gets
for helping to kidnap my mom.

68
00:03:28,350 --> 00:03:29,510
This is her punishment.

69
00:03:33,320 --> 00:03:37,290
What? Yeom San Wol's one percent share
went to Seo Rin?

70
00:03:37,420 --> 00:03:40,730
It seems Yeom San Wol sold it for money.

71
00:03:41,160 --> 00:03:42,490
What a complete fool.

72
00:03:43,030 --> 00:03:47,370
But Seo Rin acquired those shares?
Herself?

73
00:03:48,700 --> 00:03:50,800
- Then that means...
- Yes.

74
00:03:51,140 --> 00:03:53,300
It's in Ma Seo Rin's name,
but Oh Jang Mi was behind it.

75
00:03:53,610 --> 00:03:57,140
First, she impersonates Seo Rin,
and now she's going after company shares?

76
00:03:57,380 --> 00:03:59,240
Well, it's in Ma Seo Rin's name anyway.

77
00:04:00,280 --> 00:04:03,680
So this is her revenge against San Wol
for helping with her mother's kidnapping.

78
00:04:04,320 --> 00:04:05,920
That San Wol is such a fool.

79
00:04:06,820 --> 00:04:10,560
But she can't say she's Oh Jang Mi...
This is a mess.

80
00:04:10,660 --> 00:04:12,760
It's better that the one percent is
under Seo Rin's name...

81
00:04:12,760 --> 00:04:14,830
than in San Wol's hands.

82
00:04:16,490 --> 00:04:21,100
I'm sure Oh Jang Mi will try
to transfer them into her own name later.

83
00:04:21,230 --> 00:04:22,430
That clever little thing.

84
00:04:25,100 --> 00:04:28,810
By the way, good job taking care of
Ssangkal, Kang Hyuk.

85
00:04:42,550 --> 00:04:46,660
This morning, a group fight broke out
among inmates at Seoul Detention Center,

86
00:04:46,720 --> 00:04:48,630
resulting in the death
of Mr. Noh Cheol Bong.

87
00:04:48,930 --> 00:04:50,090
- Last January, Mr. Noh...
- Noh Cheol Bong?

88
00:04:50,260 --> 00:04:52,330
murdered a man named Oh
in Dream Hotel's parking garage,

89
00:04:52,400 --> 00:04:54,630
- What? That's Ssangkal.
- leaving the body in the street,

90
00:04:54,630 --> 00:04:55,630
and was arrested.

91
00:04:56,100 --> 00:04:59,570
Mr. Noh was rushed to a nearby hospital
after the fight...

92
00:04:59,640 --> 00:05:00,640
Ssangkal...

93
00:05:01,070 --> 00:05:03,310
- The other inmates...
- is dead?

94
00:05:03,310 --> 00:05:04,740
involved in the fight...

95
00:05:08,280 --> 00:05:10,580
Baek Ho! Turn on the news, quick!

96
00:05:11,080 --> 00:05:12,180
Ssangkal's dead.

97
00:05:12,550 --> 00:05:14,790
While police are treating it
as a spontaneous altercation,

98
00:05:14,850 --> 00:05:17,460
the victim's family is alleging foul play.

99
00:05:17,860 --> 00:05:18,860
No, this can't be happening.

100
00:05:19,690 --> 00:05:21,360
I can't believe CEO Chae moved so quickly.

101
00:05:22,830 --> 00:05:24,760
She thinks nothing of taking a life.

102
00:05:27,630 --> 00:05:29,300
CEO Chae is a terrifying woman.

103
00:05:30,600 --> 00:05:32,140
(Dream Hotel Murder Suspect,
Noh Cheol Bong,)

104
00:05:32,200 --> 00:05:33,200
(Dies in Brawl at Detention Center)

105
00:05:33,300 --> 00:05:34,810
(CEO Chae Hwa Young)

106
00:05:34,970 --> 00:05:36,270
Good work, Manager Lee.

107
00:05:37,240 --> 00:05:39,810
What about Ssangkal's girlfriend?
Shin Ae Ran, or whatever her name is.

108
00:05:40,040 --> 00:05:42,380
She went into hiding when Ssangkal died.

109
00:05:42,380 --> 00:05:43,580
She's in hiding?

110
00:05:44,420 --> 00:05:46,150
Find her before she teams up
with Oh Jang Mi.

111
00:05:46,250 --> 00:05:47,250
Don't worry.

112
00:05:47,750 --> 00:05:49,720
How far could she have run? It's obvious.

113
00:05:50,620 --> 00:05:51,790
Oh, right. These...

114
00:05:52,490 --> 00:05:54,630
are Seo Rin's medical records
you asked for.

115
00:05:55,930 --> 00:05:57,800
(Medication Administration Record)

116
00:05:57,900 --> 00:05:58,900
Oh Jang Mi.

117
00:05:59,160 --> 00:06:01,500
She's been acting so brazenly
all this time,

118
00:06:01,970 --> 00:06:03,740
but now it's time to teach her a lesson.

119
00:06:04,070 --> 00:06:05,940
- Should I leak this online?
- No.

120
00:06:06,140 --> 00:06:08,010
I think I'd rather do it myself.

121
00:06:08,810 --> 00:06:11,040
It's the only way
I'll get any satisfaction.

122
00:06:15,410 --> 00:06:18,220
I just saw the news,
saying that Ssangkal is dead.

123
00:06:18,520 --> 00:06:21,190
I didn't expect CEO Chae to act so fast.

124
00:06:21,320 --> 00:06:22,790
She was one step ahead of us.

125
00:06:23,620 --> 00:06:25,760
Chae Hwa Young is a monster.

126
00:06:25,820 --> 00:06:26,920
Tell me about it.

127
00:06:27,390 --> 00:06:29,260
How can she kill someone so easily?

128
00:06:29,790 --> 00:06:32,160
I don't know how she thinks
she'll ever answer for what she's done.

129
00:06:32,400 --> 00:06:35,100
She's only digging a deeper hole
for herself.

130
00:06:35,470 --> 00:06:37,970
But that doesn't mean I'm giving up.

131
00:06:38,840 --> 00:06:39,840
Of course.

132
00:06:40,300 --> 00:06:43,610
Finding his girlfriend is our priority.

133
00:06:43,610 --> 00:06:44,610
Right.

134
00:06:44,610 --> 00:06:48,110
I bet Shin Ae Ran is ready to talk
now that her boyfriend is dead.

135
00:06:48,280 --> 00:06:49,310
We need to find her fast...

136
00:06:49,310 --> 00:06:51,380
and see if Ssangkal left anything
with her.

137
00:06:54,220 --> 00:06:55,590
Oh my goodness, Chairman!

138
00:06:56,450 --> 00:06:59,720
They're saying the man
who took the fall for CEO Chae...

139
00:06:59,720 --> 00:07:00,990
died in prison.

140
00:07:01,630 --> 00:07:02,990
It was just on the breaking news!

141
00:07:03,730 --> 00:07:04,760
I heard.

142
00:07:07,800 --> 00:07:08,800
Grandfather.

143
00:07:09,370 --> 00:07:12,970
Don't you think it's strange
that the man who took the fall for Mom...

144
00:07:13,340 --> 00:07:14,610
died in prison just like that?

145
00:07:18,040 --> 00:07:21,980
Without a trial or anything,
the truth will be buried forever.

146
00:07:22,050 --> 00:07:24,580
I know. It's a scary world we live in.

147
00:07:24,850 --> 00:07:26,580
What's so scary about it?

148
00:07:27,490 --> 00:07:30,690
So, are you saying that CEO Chae
is actually a murderer?

149
00:07:31,060 --> 00:07:32,390
And to cover it up,

150
00:07:32,760 --> 00:07:35,290
she had her stand-in killed on purpose?
Is that what you're implying?

151
00:07:35,490 --> 00:07:37,260
What? No.

152
00:07:37,260 --> 00:07:40,060
- That's not what I meant.
- Mrs. Yeom!

153
00:07:40,500 --> 00:07:42,530
Watch your mouth from now on.

154
00:07:43,370 --> 00:07:45,200
The fate of the company is at stake.

155
00:07:45,470 --> 00:07:48,370
Yes, I understand, Chairman.

156
00:07:49,170 --> 00:07:51,440
Even if I told Grandfather
the whole truth,

157
00:07:51,710 --> 00:07:52,940
it would be pointless.

158
00:07:53,680 --> 00:07:55,610
To him, the company always comes first.

159
00:07:56,310 --> 00:07:58,250
No matter what terrible things
Chae Hwa Young has done,

160
00:07:58,820 --> 00:08:01,250
he'd cover it all up
for the sake of the company.

161
00:08:03,190 --> 00:08:04,420
What in the world is going on?

162
00:08:06,720 --> 00:08:09,260
Why would the man who took the fall
for CEO Chae suddenly...

163
00:08:09,590 --> 00:08:11,030
just die in prison?

164
00:08:12,660 --> 00:08:13,660
Right, Mom?

165
00:08:14,230 --> 00:08:15,300
I think that's strange, too.

166
00:08:16,630 --> 00:08:18,700
It makes no sense that the person
who confessed to being the real culprit...

167
00:08:18,900 --> 00:08:20,870
suddenly died in the detention center.

168
00:08:22,240 --> 00:08:25,040
Don't you think his death has something
to do with CEO Chae?

169
00:08:25,410 --> 00:08:26,840
What are you talking about?

170
00:08:27,380 --> 00:08:30,880
So you're saying CEO Chae went there
and killed him herself?

171
00:08:31,220 --> 00:08:34,920
Surely she wouldn't have gone that far.

172
00:08:35,190 --> 00:08:36,190
I just have a feeling...

173
00:08:36,920 --> 00:08:41,230
that CEO Chae hired someone
to take the fall for her,

174
00:08:41,760 --> 00:08:44,730
and then had him killed
in the detention center.

175
00:08:44,830 --> 00:08:46,000
Are you writing a novel?

176
00:08:46,500 --> 00:08:49,670
How could a frail woman be that monstrous?

177
00:08:49,870 --> 00:08:51,470
Even with all her money,

178
00:08:51,540 --> 00:08:53,200
that's not something you do on a whim.

179
00:08:53,340 --> 00:08:54,510
Is that what you think, Dad?

180
00:08:55,210 --> 00:08:56,970
There's more to the world
than what you see.

181
00:08:57,210 --> 00:08:59,410
I know all sorts of crazy things happen,

182
00:08:59,410 --> 00:09:00,480
but still,

183
00:09:00,880 --> 00:09:03,180
to think that someone
we know could do that...

184
00:09:04,120 --> 00:09:05,680
is just hard to believe.

185
00:09:07,650 --> 00:09:10,860
Baek Ho might be right.

186
00:09:11,260 --> 00:09:15,490
The truth will come out eventually.
I'm off to work.

187
00:09:24,700 --> 00:09:27,510
Manager Lee, you contacted
the reporters, right?

188
00:09:27,810 --> 00:09:30,170
Yes. I figured two would be enough,

189
00:09:30,270 --> 00:09:32,080
so I called two reporters
and a photographer.

190
00:09:32,180 --> 00:09:34,680
Good. Getting the story out
is what's important.

191
00:09:35,410 --> 00:09:36,750
Get the champagne ready.

192
00:09:37,320 --> 00:09:39,920
We can't kick off this show
without champagne, can we?

193
00:09:40,650 --> 00:09:41,690
Yes, ma'am.

194
00:09:45,290 --> 00:09:46,290
Oh Jang Mi.

195
00:09:47,090 --> 00:09:49,660
You must've thought I was a joke,
just letting you get away with everything.

196
00:09:51,300 --> 00:09:53,230
Fine. If you want to pick a fight,

197
00:09:53,530 --> 00:09:56,230
then the rules of the ring say
I have to fight back.

198
00:09:56,970 --> 00:09:59,470
I can't wait to see you humiliated.

199
00:10:05,540 --> 00:10:07,710
Any word from Shin Ae Ran yet, Baek Ho?

200
00:10:09,480 --> 00:10:12,080
Director Ma Seo Rin, are the rumors
of your sleeping medication use true?

201
00:10:12,150 --> 00:10:14,750
Your medical records have been leaked.
What's your response?

202
00:10:14,820 --> 00:10:17,190
We heard you received multiple injections
for insomnia.

203
00:10:18,490 --> 00:10:19,490
What are they talking about?

204
00:10:20,520 --> 00:10:21,530
Jang Mi, where are you right now?

205
00:10:21,590 --> 00:10:24,900
Did your family use its influence
to cover up the incident?

206
00:10:24,960 --> 00:10:26,900
No, that's not true!

207
00:10:26,900 --> 00:10:27,900
Please give us a statement.

208
00:10:27,900 --> 00:10:29,030
- Yes, please give us a statement.
- Director!

209
00:10:29,030 --> 00:10:30,370
- Care to comment?
- Is it true your family...

210
00:10:30,370 --> 00:10:31,400
covered up the incident?

211
00:10:31,400 --> 00:10:33,800
- Director, a comment, please.
- Just one comment, please.

212
00:10:40,140 --> 00:10:41,450
(Baek Ho)

213
00:10:51,420 --> 00:10:53,120
General Manager Kang,
what brings you here?

214
00:10:53,760 --> 00:10:54,890
Please give us a statement.

215
00:10:54,890 --> 00:10:56,430
What's happening? Are you okay?

216
00:10:56,690 --> 00:10:57,700
Hello?

217
00:10:58,400 --> 00:11:00,160
- Please say something!
- We just need one statement!

218
00:11:00,230 --> 00:11:02,730
- No pictures.
- Director, please give us a statement.

219
00:11:02,800 --> 00:11:04,700
- Just one statement, please!
- Say something!

220
00:11:04,770 --> 00:11:06,240
- Please just give us one comment.
- Give us an explanation!

221
00:11:06,300 --> 00:11:07,810
Is it true your family
covered up the incident?

222
00:11:07,870 --> 00:11:09,310
Director, make a statement!

223
00:11:19,820 --> 00:11:21,390
They're saying I was getting injections...

224
00:11:22,890 --> 00:11:23,890
Right.

225
00:11:24,860 --> 00:11:25,860
Thank you.

226
00:11:26,690 --> 00:11:28,690
I think this calls for more than
a simple "thank you."

227
00:11:29,230 --> 00:11:30,830
Why don't we have dinner tonight?

228
00:11:32,560 --> 00:11:34,470
Can I have my phone back, please?

229
00:11:36,830 --> 00:11:39,570
I'll make a reservation
and text you the details.

230
00:11:41,040 --> 00:11:43,040
I don't think I'll be free.

231
00:11:43,110 --> 00:11:45,310
But anyway, thanks for your help.

232
00:11:45,380 --> 00:11:46,580
You had insomnia?

233
00:11:47,140 --> 00:11:49,380
I didn't know that about you, Seo Rin.

234
00:11:50,950 --> 00:11:54,720
Not anymore. It was in the past
for just a little while.

235
00:11:57,760 --> 00:11:58,760
You're trembling.

236
00:11:59,720 --> 00:12:00,720
Yes, I...

237
00:12:12,200 --> 00:12:13,200
I'm...

238
00:12:13,270 --> 00:12:15,140
I'm okay.

239
00:12:16,010 --> 00:12:18,180
What's going on?
I heard a commotion outside.

240
00:12:19,340 --> 00:12:21,350
My woman is none of your concern,
Kang Baek Ho.

241
00:12:27,550 --> 00:12:30,150
It's nothing, so don't worry about it.

242
00:12:31,520 --> 00:12:32,520
General Manager Kang.

243
00:12:33,690 --> 00:12:36,290
Is the office really the place to be
throwing around terms like "my woman"?

244
00:12:36,760 --> 00:12:38,060
The company is in chaos right now,

245
00:12:38,800 --> 00:12:40,300
and I'm a member of the Legal Team.

246
00:12:40,660 --> 00:12:42,130
So naturally, it's my business
to know what's going on.

247
00:12:42,730 --> 00:12:44,100
And as the general manager,

248
00:12:44,570 --> 00:12:46,070
I expect you to separate
your personal and work life.

249
00:12:47,440 --> 00:12:49,510
- Kang Baek Ho.
- I'm sorry.

250
00:12:49,770 --> 00:12:53,110
It seems there was a leak
about my past struggles with insomnia.

251
00:12:53,880 --> 00:12:56,310
Reporters came to cover the story,
so I guess it got a little rowdy.

252
00:12:57,620 --> 00:12:59,850
I have a feeling
I know who tipped them off.

253
00:13:00,350 --> 00:13:01,450
A tip-off?

254
00:13:02,450 --> 00:13:03,990
So you're saying you know who it was?

255
00:13:05,290 --> 00:13:08,390
It's quiet out there.
I guess they all left.

256
00:13:08,790 --> 00:13:10,060
I should be going, then.

257
00:13:23,970 --> 00:13:24,980
Kang Hyuk.

258
00:13:26,410 --> 00:13:27,410
You should have a drink, too.

259
00:13:30,250 --> 00:13:32,180
It's been a while
since I've had a day this good.

260
00:13:33,020 --> 00:13:34,520
I got rid of Ssangkal,

261
00:13:34,890 --> 00:13:36,650
and I taught that
Oh Jang Mi witch a lesson.

262
00:13:36,920 --> 00:13:39,460
Oh Jang Mi seemed very rattled
by the camera flashes.

263
00:13:40,260 --> 00:13:41,890
I don't think she saw it coming.

264
00:13:51,200 --> 00:13:52,200
Bo Ra.

265
00:13:53,400 --> 00:13:54,410
That's enough crying.

266
00:14:00,910 --> 00:14:03,780
- Hey, Jang Mi.
- Bo Ra, don't cry.

267
00:14:04,110 --> 00:14:06,650
If you cry, you'll make Suk Hee sad.

268
00:14:06,720 --> 00:14:09,990
I hate you, Grandma!
I'm not playing with you anymore!

269
00:14:10,220 --> 00:14:12,590
What? Bo Ra! What's wrong?

270
00:14:13,160 --> 00:14:16,930
Bo Ra's mad now.
I wonder what's wrong with Bo Ra.

271
00:14:17,260 --> 00:14:19,530
Tae Sook, Bo Ra is crying.

272
00:14:19,730 --> 00:14:21,400
Mom, just let her be.

273
00:14:21,470 --> 00:14:23,800
She's crying. You need to go comfort her.

274
00:14:26,240 --> 00:14:27,240
Hey, Jang Mi.

275
00:14:27,540 --> 00:14:29,640
Is everything all right? Why did you call?

276
00:14:29,770 --> 00:14:31,980
Why is Bo Ra crying? Did something happen?

277
00:14:32,740 --> 00:14:33,810
No, it's just...

278
00:14:34,180 --> 00:14:36,780
she had to draw our family
at her preschool today,

279
00:14:37,210 --> 00:14:39,150
and it looks like
one of her classmates made fun of her.

280
00:14:39,420 --> 00:14:41,420
Someone made fun of her?
What did they say?

281
00:14:41,520 --> 00:14:43,020
A kid who's been to the side dish shop...

282
00:14:43,320 --> 00:14:45,360
made fun of her
by calling her grandma a dummy.

283
00:14:46,460 --> 00:14:48,390
He said since her grandma's a dummy,
Bo Ra must be one too.

284
00:14:48,560 --> 00:14:51,900
He even got the other kids
to stop playing with her.

285
00:14:52,000 --> 00:14:54,900
Since when do preschoolers gang up
on people like that?

286
00:14:55,470 --> 00:14:57,030
Poor Bo Ra must be so upset.

287
00:14:57,300 --> 00:15:00,300
- Is that Jang Mi? Let me talk to her.
- Here.

288
00:15:02,210 --> 00:15:04,410
Hey, Jang Mi. Are you getting married?

289
00:15:05,010 --> 00:15:06,080
What are you talking about?

290
00:15:07,110 --> 00:15:09,450
(CEO Chae Hwa Young)

291
00:15:10,780 --> 00:15:11,850
What is this?

292
00:15:12,320 --> 00:15:15,520
An article about marriage?
It was supposed to be about the drug use.

293
00:15:15,920 --> 00:15:18,460
I suppose the Cinderella story
is more sensational,

294
00:15:18,660 --> 00:15:20,190
so they must've focused on that angle.

295
00:15:20,260 --> 00:15:22,030
A marriage article? That's ridiculous.

296
00:15:23,260 --> 00:15:24,260
What should we do?

297
00:15:24,700 --> 00:15:26,760
- Should I tell them to pull the article?
- Wait.

298
00:15:27,460 --> 00:15:28,600
Could it be...

299
00:15:29,200 --> 00:15:32,070
that Jun Ho pulled some strings
to get this article published?

300
00:15:32,500 --> 00:15:33,840
What? Jun Ho?

301
00:15:34,940 --> 00:15:37,110
Jun Ho did say he was going
to marry Seo Rin...

302
00:15:38,080 --> 00:15:39,140
What should we do now?

303
00:15:39,540 --> 00:15:42,750
It's only because he doesn't know
she's Oh Jang Mi, not Ma Seo Rin.

304
00:15:42,810 --> 00:15:44,620
That's exactly the problem.

305
00:15:45,620 --> 00:15:47,180
But it's not like
I can just confess to Jun Ho

306
00:15:47,650 --> 00:15:51,120
that I killed Oh Jang Mi's father
and stole the twin,

307
00:15:51,320 --> 00:15:54,990
and that I'm the one
who drove her mother out of her mind.

308
00:15:55,060 --> 00:15:56,060
That's true.

309
00:15:56,490 --> 00:15:59,560
You can't just tell him,
"The Seo Rin you know is Oh Jang Mi."

310
00:15:59,630 --> 00:16:01,570
What in the world am I supposed to do?

311
00:16:04,640 --> 00:16:06,040
(Wedding Imminent:
Dream Group Heiress and Commoner)

312
00:16:06,100 --> 00:16:07,140
Hello, sir.

313
00:16:07,810 --> 00:16:09,940
Thanks again for publishing the article
so quickly.

314
00:16:10,040 --> 00:16:11,240
The photo turned out great,
don't you think?

315
00:16:11,580 --> 00:16:14,240
But is this marriage really
going to happen?

316
00:16:14,580 --> 00:16:17,450
Of course.
Why would I say it if I didn't mean it?

317
00:16:18,550 --> 00:16:22,720
We just thought it was a smokescreen
to cover up Ma Seo Rin's drug use.

318
00:16:23,950 --> 00:16:27,190
That's part of it.
She's the woman I'm marrying, after all.

319
00:16:27,990 --> 00:16:28,990
But...

320
00:16:29,390 --> 00:16:31,130
we'll be making an official announcement
about the wedding soon.

321
00:16:31,500 --> 00:16:34,260
Goodness, that's going to be a huge scoop.

322
00:16:34,800 --> 00:16:36,800
Make sure you give me a heads-up
before then, sir.

323
00:16:37,170 --> 00:16:40,470
I'll run it as a major exclusive.
I'll even clear it with my editor.

324
00:16:40,600 --> 00:16:43,110
Of course.
I appreciate your help with this,

325
00:16:43,510 --> 00:16:45,240
so you'll be the first to know.

326
00:16:53,320 --> 00:16:55,890
What does Jun Ho see
in someone like Oh Jang Mi?

327
00:16:55,890 --> 00:16:57,690
He hated her when she was Seo Rin.

328
00:16:57,890 --> 00:17:00,460
- Because her personality is different.
- Tell me something I don't know!

329
00:17:02,490 --> 00:17:03,830
Right now, there's nothing we can do.

330
00:17:05,100 --> 00:17:06,130
What are you going to do?

331
00:17:06,600 --> 00:17:07,630
Don't tell me...

332
00:17:08,000 --> 00:17:11,140
you're actually going to let Jun Ho
marry Oh Jang Mi?

333
00:17:11,240 --> 00:17:14,300
As things stand,
we have to move forward with the wedding.

334
00:17:14,570 --> 00:17:16,940
- But, ma'am...
- We're running out of time, too.

335
00:17:17,670 --> 00:17:20,080
We need to marry Jun Ho
to an heir of Chairman Ma quickly...

336
00:17:20,340 --> 00:17:21,850
so we can take control of Dream Group.

337
00:17:22,810 --> 00:17:25,020
If that means using Oh Jang Mi, so be it.

338
00:17:25,220 --> 00:17:27,180
What happens when we find Seo Rin?

339
00:17:27,450 --> 00:17:29,490
We'll swap them secretly.

340
00:17:29,620 --> 00:17:30,750
No...

341
00:17:31,160 --> 00:17:34,560
Even if Jun Ho were to find out,
it would be after the wedding.

342
00:17:34,760 --> 00:17:36,330
He'd be powerless to do anything.

343
00:17:37,460 --> 00:17:38,560
Anyway,

344
00:17:39,030 --> 00:17:43,070
as long as that boy is ambitious,
he'll have no choice but to take my side.

345
00:17:45,040 --> 00:17:46,100
Are you so sure about that?

346
00:17:46,400 --> 00:17:47,600
Jun Ho is my son.

347
00:17:48,510 --> 00:17:50,210
He could never give up on his ambition.

348
00:17:51,280 --> 00:17:54,610
He gets what he wants, no matter the cost.

349
00:17:59,920 --> 00:18:01,120
(Dream Group Heiress
and the General Manager's...)

350
00:18:01,190 --> 00:18:02,520
(Shocking Wedding Rumors)

351
00:18:08,760 --> 00:18:11,060
I'm sorry about earlier, Baek Ho.

352
00:18:11,560 --> 00:18:14,030
I panicked when all those reporters
just barged in.

353
00:18:14,670 --> 00:18:18,200
- My brother came to your rescue.
- Yes.

354
00:18:18,570 --> 00:18:20,840
But I didn't expect the news
to come out this fast.

355
00:18:21,910 --> 00:18:23,570
So you're about to marry my brother...

356
00:18:24,480 --> 00:18:27,340
That's ridiculous.
That could never happen.

357
00:18:27,810 --> 00:18:29,510
Baek Ho, you believe me, right?

358
00:18:29,910 --> 00:18:31,250
No, I don't.

359
00:18:32,480 --> 00:18:34,550
Not until you put one on my cheek.

360
00:18:41,460 --> 00:18:42,660
Okay, I believe you a little.

361
00:18:44,260 --> 00:18:46,660
But we don't have time to waste.

362
00:18:47,000 --> 00:18:49,330
You're right.
We need to strike back at Chae Hwa Young.

363
00:18:49,630 --> 00:18:50,630
We have to.

364
00:18:51,770 --> 00:18:54,440
But I feel so bad for Seo Rin.

365
00:18:54,740 --> 00:18:58,340
She must have been going through so much
to need medication just to sleep.

366
00:18:59,210 --> 00:19:00,210
Tell me about it.

367
00:19:00,540 --> 00:19:04,310
I grew up so happy,
surrounded by my family's love.

368
00:19:05,080 --> 00:19:06,620
What if we didn't have money?

369
00:19:06,680 --> 00:19:09,350
There are things you can't buy,
like love and support.

370
00:19:10,120 --> 00:19:14,260
But since Chae Hwa Young raised Seo Rin,
I guess she never had a chance.

371
00:19:15,430 --> 00:19:16,460
Wait a minute.

372
00:19:16,990 --> 00:19:18,560
What if we use this against her?

373
00:19:19,260 --> 00:19:20,300
How?

374
00:19:45,360 --> 00:19:46,360
Jun Ho.

375
00:19:46,860 --> 00:19:47,990
Have a seat.

376
00:19:48,560 --> 00:19:49,890
What's gotten into you?

377
00:19:52,730 --> 00:19:54,000
I'm just so touched.

378
00:19:54,870 --> 00:19:56,400
You're the one who asked me to dinner.

379
00:19:57,100 --> 00:19:58,770
You did want to eat
with your mom after all.

380
00:19:59,070 --> 00:20:01,870
Don't make such a big deal out of it.
There's no special reason.

381
00:20:02,340 --> 00:20:03,340
Does this mean...

382
00:20:03,770 --> 00:20:05,340
you've decided
to accept me as your mother?

383
00:20:09,580 --> 00:20:13,780
When you asked me to have a meal with you,
I felt I could take on the world, Jun Ho.

384
00:20:13,850 --> 00:20:15,420
Why are you being so dramatic?

385
00:20:16,120 --> 00:20:17,850
I just said we should have
a meal together.

386
00:20:19,260 --> 00:20:21,990
We're on the same side now,
for good. Right?

387
00:20:25,330 --> 00:20:26,460
Do you have any idea...

388
00:20:27,460 --> 00:20:28,970
how lonely I've been all this time?

389
00:20:29,300 --> 00:20:30,770
My marriage to Director Ma.

390
00:20:31,470 --> 00:20:32,640
I need you to make it happen quickly.

391
00:20:33,400 --> 00:20:35,440
I want to marry Director Ma
as soon as possible.

392
00:20:35,910 --> 00:20:36,970
Since you're my mother,

393
00:20:38,540 --> 00:20:40,740
surely you can grant a favor
for the son you abandoned, right?

394
00:20:42,010 --> 00:20:43,080
But it won't make me...

395
00:20:44,380 --> 00:20:46,150
stop resenting you or anything.

396
00:20:48,290 --> 00:20:50,250
- Jun Ho.
- Grant the requests your son is asking...

397
00:20:51,120 --> 00:20:53,260
one by one to pay back for what you did.

398
00:20:54,390 --> 00:20:55,430
That's an order.

399
00:20:59,500 --> 00:21:00,530
Alright, Jun Ho.

400
00:21:01,870 --> 00:21:03,800
If this is what my son wants so badly,

401
00:21:04,640 --> 00:21:06,000
then I'll make it happen.

402
00:21:06,740 --> 00:21:07,740
However,

403
00:21:08,370 --> 00:21:09,640
I have a condition of my own.

404
00:21:10,410 --> 00:21:11,410
What is it?

405
00:21:13,910 --> 00:21:15,580
You arrange the formal meeting
of the families.

406
00:21:16,080 --> 00:21:18,080
With the whole incident
at the detention center,

407
00:21:18,550 --> 00:21:21,850
I'm unsure what Professor Kang
and his wife would think of me.

408
00:21:22,090 --> 00:21:25,220
Actually, it would be better
if I stayed out of it.

409
00:21:27,860 --> 00:21:28,930
Here.

410
00:21:30,060 --> 00:21:31,830
Jun Ho, did you have something
you wanted to say?

411
00:21:34,300 --> 00:21:36,100
I'm going to marry Director Ma.

412
00:21:40,340 --> 00:21:42,010
Please invite CEO Chae to our home.

413
00:21:42,810 --> 00:21:46,040
It can serve as a family meeting,
and you can discuss the marriage with her.

414
00:21:48,250 --> 00:21:51,280
Jun Ho, do you really have to marry
into that family?

415
00:21:51,620 --> 00:21:54,320
Yes. I love Director Ma.

416
00:21:55,020 --> 00:21:56,820
I have to marry her, no matter what.

417
00:21:57,490 --> 00:21:59,320
- Don't try to stop me.
- Jun Ho.

418
00:22:00,120 --> 00:22:01,120
What is it?

419
00:22:01,890 --> 00:22:03,360
Are you done with Oh Jang Mi,

420
00:22:04,190 --> 00:22:06,200
and now you're going after Director Ma?

421
00:22:06,330 --> 00:22:07,630
Does Seo Rin even want to marry you?

422
00:22:07,900 --> 00:22:09,400
Or does what Seo Rin wants not matter?

423
00:22:09,400 --> 00:22:11,200
This has nothing to do with you.

424
00:22:11,330 --> 00:22:14,340
I'm the one marrying Seo Rin.
Why would you get involved?

425
00:22:14,810 --> 00:22:18,240
Why are you yelling?
Just talk to him nicely.

426
00:22:18,910 --> 00:22:21,110
Baek Ho is just asking
because he's curious.

427
00:22:22,610 --> 00:22:23,650
Alright, Jun Ho.

428
00:22:24,050 --> 00:22:28,950
If you're really set on this,
I'll invite CEO Chae over and talk to her.

429
00:22:38,800 --> 00:22:41,030
(CEO Chae)

430
00:22:49,240 --> 00:22:52,210
Why would the man who took the fall
for CEO Chae suddenly...

431
00:22:52,210 --> 00:22:53,440
just die in prison?

432
00:22:58,010 --> 00:22:59,180
(CEO Chae)

433
00:23:03,850 --> 00:23:06,620
Did Nam Bong just decline my call?

434
00:23:09,490 --> 00:23:11,030
What am I going to do with that man?

435
00:23:11,830 --> 00:23:15,830
It would be a disaster if he mentioned
that I called him before the accident.

436
00:23:17,870 --> 00:23:20,770
So you're saying you ended up
blowing all your money?

437
00:23:20,870 --> 00:23:23,840
Stop nagging me, you brat!
Believe me, I feel worse than you do.

438
00:23:23,840 --> 00:23:25,510
What gives you the right
to yell like that?

439
00:23:25,640 --> 00:23:28,810
Because of you, I never get any peace.

440
00:23:28,810 --> 00:23:29,850
What was that?

441
00:23:29,880 --> 00:23:31,750
You were supposed to look for Oh Jang Mi.

442
00:23:32,120 --> 00:23:34,280
Why would you go off
and foolishly lose all your money instead?

443
00:23:34,350 --> 00:23:37,220
What do you mean, "foolishly"?
I met her brother, Oh Tae Pyung...

444
00:23:40,990 --> 00:23:42,130
Hey, Hong Ju.

445
00:23:42,130 --> 00:23:44,760
What if we focus our search
on that side dish shop?

446
00:23:45,400 --> 00:23:48,770
- What?
- That side dish shop is her family's.

447
00:23:48,930 --> 00:23:50,970
A bird always returns to its nest,

448
00:23:51,470 --> 00:23:54,000
so Oh Jang Mi is bound to come back
home eventually, right?

449
00:23:54,300 --> 00:23:56,310
Instead of looking for her
in all the wrong places...

450
00:23:56,370 --> 00:23:58,940
CEO Chae is going crazy
looking for Oh Jang Mi right now.

451
00:23:59,210 --> 00:24:00,740
As if she'd show her face there.

452
00:24:01,210 --> 00:24:02,410
Whatever! Seriously...

453
00:24:04,950 --> 00:24:06,780
That girl gets more and more out of hand.

454
00:24:07,180 --> 00:24:08,790
How dare she treat her mother like this?

455
00:24:11,350 --> 00:24:12,790
But it's so strange.

456
00:24:13,390 --> 00:24:15,960
Why would CEO Chae be looking
for Oh Jang Mi now?

457
00:24:16,230 --> 00:24:17,860
Especially since she's the one
who gave birth to the twins.

458
00:24:19,760 --> 00:24:21,530
I just don't get what's going on.

459
00:24:28,740 --> 00:24:30,740
(Director Ma Seo Rin)

460
00:24:32,110 --> 00:24:34,280
If you know anything about being a twin,

461
00:24:34,810 --> 00:24:38,180
then you might know where Oh Jang Mi is.

462
00:24:40,820 --> 00:24:41,890
Why are you looking at me like that?

463
00:24:43,050 --> 00:24:44,050
It's nothing.

464
00:24:45,120 --> 00:24:46,160
By the way, Director Ma...

465
00:24:46,560 --> 00:24:48,760
Do you happen to know someone
named Oh Jang Mi?

466
00:24:49,590 --> 00:24:51,460
What? Oh Jang Mi?

467
00:24:52,800 --> 00:24:53,830
Never mind if you don't.

468
00:24:57,970 --> 00:25:00,170
She definitely looked like
she recognized the name.

469
00:25:00,800 --> 00:25:02,810
(Director Ma Seo Rin)

470
00:25:04,140 --> 00:25:06,380
Director Ma,
we're all set for the interview.

471
00:25:06,910 --> 00:25:07,910
Really?

472
00:25:10,550 --> 00:25:11,550
What?

473
00:25:11,620 --> 00:25:14,150
Seo Rin's holding a press conference...

474
00:25:14,150 --> 00:25:15,690
to apologize
for taking sleeping medication?

475
00:25:15,750 --> 00:25:18,920
Yes. It looks like it's about to start
in the conference room.

476
00:25:19,820 --> 00:25:22,760
She walked right into my trap.
Serves her right.

477
00:25:23,330 --> 00:25:26,330
That's what happens when you get cocky
and challenge me.

478
00:25:27,000 --> 00:25:29,000
The nerve of her, sending me to jail.

479
00:25:30,030 --> 00:25:32,440
Let her feel the heat
from the entire country.

480
00:25:32,740 --> 00:25:34,670
(CEO Chae Hwa Young)

481
00:25:34,740 --> 00:25:37,640
It would only be polite for us
to go watch this entertaining show, right?

482
00:25:38,810 --> 00:25:39,810
Oh Jang Mi.

483
00:25:48,250 --> 00:25:52,220
First of all, I am deeply sorry...

484
00:25:53,120 --> 00:25:55,060
for causing everyone so much concern.

485
00:26:13,840 --> 00:26:15,810
(CEO Chae Relied on Sleep Medication
Since Her Acting Days)

486
00:26:15,880 --> 00:26:18,450
(Allegations of Mother-Daughter
Drug Abuse Spreads)

487
00:26:18,750 --> 00:26:19,750
What is this?

488
00:26:20,280 --> 00:26:21,350
Director Ma Seo Rin.

489
00:26:21,850 --> 00:26:25,060
Now that a past interview
with CEO Chae Hwa Young has resurfaced,

490
00:26:25,560 --> 00:26:28,090
speculative articles are circulating,
suggesting that you and your mother...

491
00:26:28,160 --> 00:26:29,830
were both using sleeping medication.

492
00:26:29,830 --> 00:26:30,830
Is this true?

493
00:26:31,430 --> 00:26:32,760
The inevitable has happened.

494
00:26:34,100 --> 00:26:35,270
I will tell you...

495
00:26:36,130 --> 00:26:37,470
the entire truth...

496
00:26:38,600 --> 00:26:40,740
about my mother and me.

497
00:26:43,210 --> 00:26:44,570
What is this fake news?

498
00:26:44,980 --> 00:26:47,640
And what on earth is that brat
about to say?

499
00:26:49,150 --> 00:26:50,380
My mother...

500
00:26:51,210 --> 00:26:55,320
has been under extreme stress
ever since her acting days.

501
00:26:56,050 --> 00:26:59,490
And during her long tenure as CEO,

502
00:27:00,160 --> 00:27:01,390
the immense responsibility...

503
00:27:02,090 --> 00:27:03,960
and a number of scandals
have weighed heavily on her.

504
00:27:04,460 --> 00:27:06,800
Could you please elaborate?

505
00:27:07,330 --> 00:27:09,330
Are you accusing your own mother?

506
00:27:10,300 --> 00:27:12,200
Accuse her? Don't be absurd.

507
00:27:12,540 --> 00:27:15,110
As her daughter, I couldn't just...

508
00:27:16,010 --> 00:27:18,210
stand by and watch her suffer.

509
00:27:19,910 --> 00:27:21,340
It's true that...

510
00:27:21,540 --> 00:27:23,580
I was the one
who was prescribed sleeping medication.

511
00:27:24,810 --> 00:27:26,980
Even though I saw my mother suffering
from insomnia,

512
00:27:27,450 --> 00:27:28,990
I know what I did was wrong.

513
00:27:30,990 --> 00:27:32,820
So please, blame me.

514
00:27:33,390 --> 00:27:34,620
But as for my mother,

515
00:27:35,560 --> 00:27:37,060
please find it in your hearts
to forgive her.

516
00:27:38,060 --> 00:27:40,330
Are you saying CEO Chae Hwa Young...

517
00:27:40,330 --> 00:27:42,670
had sleeping medication
prescribed in your name...

518
00:27:42,830 --> 00:27:44,830
and then took the injections herself?

519
00:27:50,170 --> 00:27:51,670
CEO Chae, is that true?

520
00:27:51,940 --> 00:27:53,180
- Is your daughter being truthful?
- Any comment?

521
00:27:53,240 --> 00:27:55,710
- CEO, is it really true?
- We need a comment!

522
00:27:59,850 --> 00:28:01,950
Chae Hwa Young. An eye for an eye.

523
00:28:02,450 --> 00:28:05,660
I'm just paying you back
for the despicable trick you pulled.

524
00:28:13,660 --> 00:28:15,130
You wicked witch!

525
00:28:15,200 --> 00:28:17,730
(CEO Chae Hwa Young)

526
00:28:17,800 --> 00:28:20,370
You nasty, insolent brat!

527
00:28:20,800 --> 00:28:23,140
How dare you pull such a sly stunt
in front of my Jun Ho!

528
00:28:50,530 --> 00:28:52,070
(The First Man)

529
00:28:52,140 --> 00:28:54,840
By the way,
is Jang Mi really marrying your brother?

530
00:28:55,070 --> 00:28:57,840
You like Baek Ho, don't you?
So just go for it.

531
00:28:57,910 --> 00:28:59,380
I'll back you up.

532
00:28:59,540 --> 00:29:00,910
Baek Ho, you've known...

533
00:29:00,910 --> 00:29:03,880
this whole time that Director Ma
and Oh Jang Mi were twins.

534
00:29:04,080 --> 00:29:05,420
Why are you keeping it a secret
from everyone?

535
00:29:05,680 --> 00:29:06,780
What are you getting at?

536
00:29:06,780 --> 00:29:08,950
You know where Oh Jang Mi is, don't you?

537
00:29:09,320 --> 00:29:10,520
You insolent brat.

538
00:29:10,590 --> 00:29:13,060
You're getting this worked up
over a little embarrassment?

539
00:29:13,060 --> 00:29:15,990
- Why you...
- Grandfather! Mom hit me!

540
00:29:16,330 --> 00:29:18,500
Are you out of your mind?

541
00:29:22,800 --> 00:29:24,800
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
